In [[planetary geology]], a '''chasma''' (plural ''chasmata'', meaning "a cleft, an abyss" in [[Greek language|Greek]]) refers to long, narrow, steep sided depressions on other [[planet]]s and [[natural satellite|moons]].

==Other uses==
* [[Chasma Spring|Chasma]] means ''Water Spring'' in [[Persian language|Persian]] and [[Urdu language|Urdu]].
* [[Chashma (Pakistan)|Chasma]] is a city in Pakistan.
* A [[yawn|chasma]] is a synonym of a [[yawn]]<ref name=Heusner>A. Price Heusner. YAWNING AND ASSOCIATED PHENOMENA. ''Physiological Review'' 1946: '''25'''; 156-168. [http://baillement.com/recherche/heusner.pdf Online pdf-version]</ref>.


